==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Discriminating
<hw>Dis*crim"i*na`ting</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Marking a difference; distinguishing.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Dis*crim"i*na`ting*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And finds with keen <qex>discriminating</qex> sight,⟦br⟧
Black's not so black; -- nor white so very white.</q>
<rj><qau>Canning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>making careful or fine distinctions, especially as
to quality or accuracy; <as>as, a <ex>discriminating</ex>
observer</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> discerning, perspicacious.</syn>
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>having a refined taste or excellent judgment;
<as>as, a <ex>discriminating</ex> taste</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Discrimination</ent>⟦br⟧
